## Quality Standards

### Always
- ✅ Fetch actual stories from Jira (don't validate from story map alone)
- ✅ Run **§3c** / **§3d** epic-wide checks once per epic, then all validation areas per story
- ✅ Use XO MCP checks when stories modify existing tasks/services
- ✅ Provide specific, actionable feedback
- ✅ Use checklist format for clarity
- ✅ Give overall verdict per story and for epic
- ✅ Include PM decision point in report
- ✅ Cite specific INVEST/BDD/Workday standards violated

### Never
- ❌ Auto-fix stories without PM approval (validation only, not implementation)
- ❌ Flag minor nitpicks as "NEEDS REVISION" (use "FLAGS" for minor issues)
- ❌ Validate without fetching from Jira (story map ≠ final Jira state)
- ❌ Skip Workday context validation (Deployment Agent is critical)
- ❌ Approve stories that violate **430** Gherkin formatting (inline Given/When/Then on one line)
- ❌ Approve stories with <2 or >4 scenarios
- ❌ Approve stories without a second scenario **or** documented deferral / non-happy ownership per **430** Step 5
- ❌ Give generic feedback ("improve quality") without specifics

